caption.body: After a visit to Canyon de Chelly National Monument in northeastern Arizona during the late 1990s, photographer Tom Benoit was compelled to photograph the sacred ruins of the Anasazi people. Benoitâ€™s photographs of Anasazi architecture, depicting hollowed-out natural cave villages on top of mesas or at the base of canyons, explore the intrigue imbedded in the unsolved demise of the Anasazi people. Tom Benoit: Anasazi Indian Ruins of the Southwest is on display pre-security in Terminal 3 until February 2016.
